expected picture of the earth’s future.<br>
<br>
We all know that in 6 or 7 billion years the sun will go Red Giant and the earth will be uninhabitable. What I suspect most of us didn’t know is that the earth will become uninhabitable long before this time.<br>
<br>
In fact it’s almost (in geological terms) “Game Over” now.<br>
<br>
In less than 1 billion years the earth will no longer be able to support plant life due to atmospheric changes brought on by a gradually warming sun.<br>
<br>
Recent theories suggest that life evolved early in the earths life, practically as soon as it became cool enough to exist, for billions of years nothing more complicated than bacteria existed then suddenly, around 500 million years ago there occurred an explosion of complex multi-cellular life and in less than a billion years it will all be over, in geological terms, just as we were getting started!<br>
<br>
It is strange, there is no conceivable reason why I should feel particularly upset about this but somehow, nevertheless, I feel that Gaia has been somewhat short changed.<br>
